{"word":"ἐξορκόω","slug":"ἐξορκόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξορκόω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ώσω</el>) </el><p/><i>to swear</i> a person, <i>administer an oath to</i> one, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, or <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ἐξορκούντων οἱ πρυτάνεις</el> Foed. <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; followed by <el>ἦ μήν</el> (ionic <el>ἦ μέν</el>) <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to make</i> one <i>swear by</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/>"}]}